Hi all who wonder about this style change applied to many other or sometime all cells.

I ran into the same issue . When I changed the numFmt of a cell after save all the cells had this formatting.
After a couple of hour "search/try/error" cycle I found this in the [documantation](https://github.com/exceljs/exceljs?tab=readme-ov-file#styles)

As you can see in the caveat section they share the same object under the hood if possible. Stated that on load they use the shared style object if possible. So this is the answer why it changes and why to your last modification.

What I have done is a bit hacky but used the util function from this lib.
```ts
import Excel from 'exceljs';
import ExcelUtils from 'exceljs/lib/utils/copy-style.js';

function someFunction(cell: Excel.Cell, numFmt: string) {
  cell.style = ExcelUtils.copyStyle(cell.style);
  cell.numFmt = numFmt;
}
```

I don't know even this lib is maintained or developed, but maybe a flag for read or on workBook could handle this behavour trait better tha all the time manually copy the style...

But for sure the documatetion should give more visibility to this behaviour. :)
